Pink coral, cedar trees, and various fish species are set to receive increased protection, as per a UN agency report.
Overexploitation threatens Brazilian lobsters and sawfish, prompting calls for trade halts.
The EU advocates for permits on European eels and spiny dogfish to manage fisheries.
Coral reefs, vital for biodiversity, face extinction risks due to climate change.
Conservation efforts are crucial, with experts emphasizing sustainable practices.
The global trade in red coral is now regulated to safeguard its future.
